replyContent: Ads are switched off in paid version, but it shares codebase with free version. So SDKs for ad networks are included in package, but completely switched off in paid version. As you can see, there are no ads served in paid version. Feel free to email if you need further clarification.

I have a couple of their products and like them very much.  It is incredibly easy to use, but COULD be improved by: 1. Enabling the user to specify folders for their media; 2. Enabling the user to choose a view of their FAVORITE folders simultaneously on one page; and 3. Enabling the user to choose different colors.  I like the color orange, but it doesn't look right on my screen (maybe it's just my eyesight).  In regards to the aforementioned, I have different media folders than the original default folders.  So it takes me a long time to find my images for example - as they are in a different folder than the default.  I'd like to be able to MAKE FOLDER DEFAULT for images.  If 1. were fixed, then 2. really wouldn't be an issue.  And in respect to colors, well there's no menu per se so you can't change the view in any way.  It would benefit by offering a couple choices.  That being said, this is an incredibly easy to use program that works right out of the box.  You can't go wrong with the small purchase price!

Okay, I'm fairly technologically sophisticated, but not an expert. Upon first use, I follow the instructions to type in a web address on my bluetooth connected computer. 'Waiting for AD block extension comes up' and it gets stuck there - forever. Now the developer, Paul Dyble, has written a blog stating why people who rate this as 'it sux' are wrong. I think Mr. Dyble is blowing smoke. He lists about 10 things to try in sequential order if you're having problems. You'll need to be highly proficient in home networks to understand it. The first 'fix' is if you're using the app won't work if the web browser on your computer and your android device are using the same wifi network. Dyble says "if they are, you might as well quit right here." So, if you don't know how to configure 2 wifi networks with your router, you're screwed. Other solutions are more complex. Apps that 'just work' are what people want and pay for. This app 'just sux'. Waste of time and money.
